34. Replace all occurrences of a specific word with another word in a string using regular expressions in
PHP.

CODE:
<?php
$text = "PHP is great. I love PHP because PHP is powerful.";
$pattern = "/PHP/";         // The word to find
$replacement = "Python";    // The word to replace it with

$result = preg_replace($pattern, $replacement, $text);

echo $result;
?>

OUTPUT:
Python is great. I love Python because Python is powerful.
